<br>
Waaaay back when the FA 3927's and dual-wield were nerfed, I made my Engie and my Doctor both MA types. BY that I mean they maxxed their MA skill and stopped carrying weps.<br>
<br>
Well, that was a very bad idea, for reasons I'm sure you folks need explained less than any other audience in the world.<br>
<br>
So both those ladies sat in the bench for a loooong time while I played Publius. Recently I've rehabilitated them both. Now Hildy, my doc, is just not a fighting character at all, so it's not an issue.<br>
<br>
Didelphis, my engineer, is another matter.<br>
<br>
Having learned more about the game, and spent a LOT of time at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://virral.clansupport.com">The Workshop</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, I have very different ideas on how to play an engie than I did 6 months ago.<br>
<br>
Engies who are smart do NOT try to do much damage themselves, because it draws aggro. Engies who are smart stand back and plink away to entertain themselves, so they don't fall asleep of sheer boredom while their bot does the killing. Engies who are smart pick a weapon that will boost their stats!<br>
<br>
So I have Del fall back on her basic pistol skills. W00t, 15 points per hit, with a ring and a damage buff, w00h00!!<br>
<br>
Having plenty of tie to notice stuff, while the bot methodically dismembers my <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> villian du jour</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I notice something weird is going on with the attack bars. I hit Y to hide the shortcut bar, which is in front, and I find that she has TWO attack bars going. One for the pistol, and one for fists, since her MA skill is over 120.<br>
<br>
OK, no problem, I zone once and the fist attack bar goes away, so it's not interfering with her lilliputtian pistol attacks. (Recently I got her a Q60 gluegun strapped on, which is more fun).<br>
<br>
So, having talked you all the way around behind Robin Hood's barn, I'm finally ready to get to the point here.<br>
<br>
Once this fix is in, how do you STOP your character from punching if you don't want them to?<br>
<br>
Keep in mind, those punch attack bars cycle, and interfere with your other weapon's timing, even when you are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> out of range of melee attacks</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Obviously, this isn't a big deal for my engie, she's going to do crap for damage no matter what. But I can sure envision situations where it might be very important. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/unutbar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NutBar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>They call me Bruce.</span><br>  Posts: 377<br> <font color=#660000>(2/20/02 5:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1690.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://files.sobservers.com/New%20Files/nut/scary2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NEWS FLASH!! debuff/zone/bug fixed!</span><hr size=1> What is you ma skill?  If it's lower than 140 try using MA incompetance on yourself.  <br>
